132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 633
H.P. 401 House of Representatives, February 25, 2025
An Act Concerning the Restoration of Electricity During
Emergencies for Certain Medically Vulnerable Individuals Who
Rely on Electronic Medical Apparatuses
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 20, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Energy, Utilities and Technology pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to
Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative FRIEDMANN of Bar Harbor.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §3144, sub-§2, ¶E, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 120, §1, is
3 amended to read:
4 E. Procedures for deployment of internal and external resources during an emergency,
5 including field employees, supplies and equipment needed; and
6 Sec. 2. 35-A MRSA §3144, sub-§2, ¶F, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 120, §1, is
7 amended to read:
8 F. Provisions to ensure the safety of the employees and external contractors engaged
9 in emergency response efforts.; and
10 Sec. 3. 35-A MRSA §3144, sub-§2, ¶G is enacted to read:
11 G. Procedures for the identification of and outreach plans regarding customers who
12 have a documented need of electricity for essential medical equipment, including an
13 apnea monitor for an infant, a cuirass respirator, a hemodialysis machine, an
14 intravenous feeding machine, an intravenous infusion machine, an oxygen
15 concentrator, a positive-pressure respirator, a respirator or ventilator, a rocking bed
16 respirator, an aspirator, a tank-type respirator or any other medical equipment
17 necessary for an individual whose medical condition is likely to be significantly
18 triggered or exacerbated by a continued loss of electricity in a way that will adversely
19 impact that individual's health.
20 SUMMARY
2211 This bill requires investor-owned transmission and distribution utilities to include in
2222 their emergency response plans procedures for the identification of and outreach plans
2233 regarding customers who have a documented need of electricity for essential medical
2244 equipment.
